The paper discusses the application of formal concept analysis to hypertext systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also covers the summarization and scaling of networked information resources, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The creation of conceptual links and the use of faceted analysis techniques in library science classification are also discussed, which could be categorized under natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
